The Maroela Makiti was back at the Hervormde Kerk Nelspruit on Friday February 25. The event was held on the church grounds and welcomed visitors from 15:00 on Friday until 22:00 that day. The event garnered a small crowd as well as a few food stands, including stalls selling marula beer. ALSO READ: UPDATE: Grandson appears in Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court for grandmother’s murder The market set out a row of tables for marketgoers to sit, eat and drink at, while watching some live music as the evening progressed. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram